{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Fungi uptake extracellular ferrous iron (Fe2+) using a bipartite high-affinity transporter consisting of a multicopper ferroxidase associated with a membrane permease which translocates generated ferric iron (Fe3+) into the cytosol. The Saccharomyces cerevisiae (Baker's yeast) iron permease FTR1 is a plasma membrane permease for high-affinity iron uptake [[cite:PUB00015322]]. FTR1, together with multicopper oxidase FET3, mediate high-affinity iron uptake. Schizosaccharomyces pombe Fio1 (ferrous iron oxidase) and Fip1 (ferriferous permease), share significant similarity to FET3 and FTR1 from S. cerevisiae [[cite:PUB00070773]]. In Neosartorya fumigata, the high affinity iron permease is known as FtrA [[cite:PUB00089625]].</p>\n\n<p>Many bacteria possess Fe2+ transporters with functional similarities to the FET3-FTR1 system. Escherichia coli encodes an EfeUOB transporter where EfeU is homologous to the high-affinity iron permease FTR1 of Saccharomyces cerevisiae [[cite:PUB00070776], [cite:PUB00067523]]. Bacillus subtilis encodes similar proteins, but not identical to the E. coli EfeUOB transporter components. B. subtilis EfeUOB uses a transport system that permits the high-affinity acquisition of both Fe2+ and Fe3+ [[cite:PUB00070775]].</p>\n\n<p>This entry also includes the vacuolar iron transporter FTH1 [[cite:PUB00070777]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR31632" "IRON TRANSPORTER FTH1"}, "pfam" {"PF03239" "Iron permease FTR1 family"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Iron permease FTR1/Fip1/EfeU", "short" "FTR1/Fip1/EfeU"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 65, "proteomes" 4012, "taxa" 16178, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 18419, "sets" 0, "proteins" 18359, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 13547}, "path